         Here I thought I was being dry and dispassionate with that post. Guess I can't win.<P>The class/race/discipline/level system worries me, too, but that's only because I don't know exactly how it's supposed to work. So do a lot of other things (how its system will be perceived by those whose entire PvP concept is based on UO or EQ is one of them.<P>My worrying is not going to make much difference if Wolfpack isn't going to take what I say into account when designing the game. They've made it very clear at nearly every turn that what I say or think about what they should or shouldn't do means very, very little. Except when I misconstrue something that they've said they're planning; then they're VERY interested.<P>I would like nothing better to be a partner in shaping what will be a very important game, sink or swim. If I don't, I hope some other knowledgeable players do, because the worst thing Wolfpack could do design-wise is to keep experienced players out of the loop.<P>On the other hand, for every player who's able to think outside the box of his or her's own experience, there are 40 gimps who think, "u just make uo but haev it suk less!11!" Go read the official Shadowbane forums, where that ratio is well represented. This is part and parcel why Wolfpack doesn't say very much about this shit.<P>Most Shadowbane fans 'in the know' have grown rather dispassionate, as a result. They've gone through the 'oh wow' period, and little can impress them anymore, short of the opportunity to play in a beta.<P>And the beat goes on.<P>J.<BR>damned vulpine<BR><a href="http://sb.xrgaming.net/" target="_blank">http://sb.xrgaming.net/</a>
